PHASE 2: BUILD THE APPLICATION
======================================================================

Step 2.1: Build Release Version in Visual Studio
------------------------------------------------
1. Open Visual Studio

2. Open the Solution:
   - File → Open → Project/Solution
   - Navigate to your project folder
   - Open store parts.sln

3. Set Build Configuration to Release:
   - In the toolbar dropdown, change "Debug" to "Release"

4. Build the Solution:
   - Build → Build Solution
   - OR press Ctrl + Shift + B

5. Wait for "Build succeeded" message

6. Verify output files exist in:
   store parts\bin\Release\
   - store parts.exe
   - MySql.Data.dll
   - Other .dll files

---

Step 2.2: Create Installer with Inno Setup
------------------------------------------
1. Download Inno Setup from: https://jrsoftware.org/isdl.php

2. Install Inno Setup

3. Open StorePartsSetup.iss from your project folder

4. Press Ctrl + F9 to compile

5. Installer will be created in: InstallerOutput\StorePartsSetup_v2.0.0.exe

